Overview

NotionWealth Intelligence is an agentic decision platform that transforms fragmented financial disclosures into a continuously learning research, risk, and capital-intelligence system.

It is not a chatbot.

It is a multi-agent cognition layer designed to support:
	â€¢	financial research
	â€¢	risk and anomaly detection
	â€¢	competitive intelligence
	â€¢	portfolio-level reasoning
	â€¢	capital allocation modeling
	â€¢	traceable, replayable decision workflows

The core problem this system addresses is institutional cognition:

How do we build AI systems that do not just answer questions, but maintain memory, coordinate specialized agents, verify claims, replay past reasoning, and support real strategic and capital decisions?

â¸»

System Capabilities

ðŸ”¹ Ingestion Agents
	â€¢	Ingest 10-Ks, 10-Qs, earnings decks, transcripts, and market PDFs
	â€¢	Parse, chunk, embed, and persist financial knowledge
	â€¢	Extract both:
	â€¢	semantic memory (vector store)
	â€¢	structured financial facts

ðŸ”¹ Multi-Layer Memory
	â€¢	Semantic memory: qualitative, contextual, narrative knowledge
	â€¢	Structured financial memory: metrics, segments, growth, risks
	â€¢	Research memory: persisted research sessions and traces

ðŸ”¹ Specialized Research Agents
	â€¢	Financial agent: performance, growth, margins, segments
	â€¢	Risk & anomaly agent: regulatory, operational, financial drift
	â€¢	Competitive intelligence agent: cross-company positioning
	â€¢	Portfolio agent: exposure, concentration, strategy themes

ðŸ”¹ Control Plane
	â€¢	Task routing and orchestration
	â€¢	Verification and evidence attachment
	â€¢	Research session generation
	â€¢	Trace, audit, and replay support

ðŸ”¹ Synthesis & Decision Agents
	â€¢	Investment memo generation
	â€¢	Capital allocation modeling
	â€¢	Portfolio-level reasoning
	â€¢	Strategic scenario construction

ðŸ”¹ Research Replay Engine
	â€¢	Persisted research sessions
	â€¢	Replay and diff against new data
	â€¢	Institutional learning and audit trail

ðŸ”¹ Product Layer (UI)
	â€¢	Run research workflows
	â€¢	View verified outputs
	â€¢	Replay past decisions
	â€¢	Generate memos and portfolio briefs

